I used to be a serial networker so I get it. I cohosted the largest networking events in the state of Hawaii, I was addicted too. 

It was a relief when a friend told me a years ago “Gene you can stop now. You’re not here to network anymore. People are here to network with you.”

I still recognize my privilege in the job safety I am thankfully enjoying, as well as the stage in my career where I no longer feel compelled to network and “be seen” in person. I sympathize with anyone who still feels they need to do this and can’t.

as a newly medically disabled and highly immunocompromised person (again I have cancer), it’s pretty wild to see event organizers in the industry I cover basically forget about people like me. https://t.co/tXqwzGBnGP

Matthew goes beyond jargon and marketing smoke and mirrors to shine a light on the challenges of evolving the internet. His book is essential reading to anyone interested not just in what digital life may evolve into, but how we’ve already evolved with it throughout time.

This is the big reason why @ballmatthew is so influential in shaping our understanding of a conceptual metaverse: he is a skilled communicator and writer with clarity of thought. His book is a showcase of this talent as he traces the contours of our theoretical, collective future https://t.co/dL7ZqFmoLD
